owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

registerNewLock(address,string,uint256,u.details: Each user can have multiple locks identified by lock id. Reverts in the following cases: - Duplicated lock id for a user. - `unlockDates` and `unlockPercents` length don't match. - `unlockPercents` sum is not equal to 100 (100%).

params.amount: amount of tokens to be locked.
params.unlockDates: an array of durations (in days) that some amount of locked tokens to be unlocked.
params.unlockPercents: an array of percentages of total locked tokens to be unlocked at corresponding `unlockDates`.
params.user: user receiving tokens when they are unlocked.

release(string).details: User (sender) can withdraw unlocked tokens by calling this function. This function will release locked tokens from multiple lock phases that meets unlock requirements Reverts in the following cases: - Lock id not exists - No tokens to be withdrawn including:     + All lock phases are already released     + Do not meet next unlock requirements - Amount of tokens that this smart contract holds is insufficient. In this case, users should contact the owner of the token.

params.lockId: Lock id that users want to withdraw

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

registerNewLock(address,string,uint256,u.notice: Register a new lock for a user
